🧠 Complete Recon Workflow (WHOIS + DNS)

This is exactly how professionals do passive recon 👇

🟢 Step 1 — WHOIS Lookup
Tools:
whois example.com
Whois
Online tools (ICANN WHOIS)
What to look for:
Registrar (e.g., ICANN regulated)
Creation date → old domains = more trust
Expiry date → possible takeover risk
Name servers → move to DNS step

🟢 Step 2 — Extract Name Servers

Example output:

ns1.cloudflare.com
ns2.cloudflare.com

👉 This tells you:

Hosting provider (e.g., Cloudflare)

🟢 Step 3 — DNS Enumeration
Tools:
nslookup
dig
dnsrecon
Amass

🔍 Basic Commands
1. Get IP Address
nslookup example.com

2. Get All Records
dig example.com ANY

3. Get Mail Servers
dig example.com MX

🟢 Step 4 — Subdomain Enumeration

👉 Goal: Find hidden assets

Tools:
Subfinder
Amass

Example:

dev.example.com
admin.example.com
api.example.com

🟢 Step 5 — Reverse DNS Lookup

👉 Find domains hosted on same IP

Command:
dig -x <IP>

🟢 Step 6 — Zone Transfer (Advanced)

👉 Check if DNS server is misconfigured

dig axfr @ns1.example.com example.com

⚠️ If it works → FULL domain exposure (rare but critical)

🟢 Step 7 — Analyze TXT Records
dig example.com TXT

👉 Look for:

SPF records
API keys (sometimes leaked)
Verification tokens


